AWS Lambda = You write your code in a function and AWS lambda deploys for you

S3 bucket = ( completely service ) = used for storing files and static content + scales depending on how much data stored 

AWS Cognito = helps manage user authentication -> making it easy to manage sign in / logins in your app

DynamoDB = ( no sql ) fully managed server less + no sql database -> scales automatically ( no provision / manage db servers )

Aurora Serverless = (sql based) managed DB that scales up and down capacity and pay for what you use (capacity wise)(relational)

Fargate = run containers w/out managing the servers - normally you manage the ec2 instances (vm’s) they run on but fargate handles the infra

Step Functions = help coordinate workflow like lambda functions & ECS tasks , they make sure task run in order 

API Gateway (can trigger lambda functions )= central point for API requests where the api request is received the api gateway then assigns it to the right backend service and returns response to user.
* Api gateway receives request -> lambda function runs and returns result to use *

[AWS SNS] (simple notification service) = designed to send message to multiple recipients at once -> (push notifications)
[AWS SQS] (queue service ) = delivers message in queue between services  -> one by one and until it is picked up (reliable)
